channel.title: How to put in new items?
channel.description:
How do i change items from nulls to the right items?
I mean, whats the code in client.java, i already have the item id's

item.title: How to put in new items?
item.dc:creator: @N11 -N-
item.description:
@N11 wrote:

[quote=“SkillersDream, post:12, topic:243505”][quote author=f1rey wav3 link=topic=319820.msg2534911#msg2534911 date=1226698453]
Ok, maybe you can help me out here

I downloaded a model

I have the wear and drop files

I copied the ints and i have the right ones down

When i try to spawn or pickup the item on my server though it says this item does not exist

I also put the models in my models folder on my source
[/quote]

the models folder is on the client to…and if it says item does not exist it’s because your server dosn’t let you spawn that high.[/quote]

Haha and that. A good Idea is to do,

Server source > item.cfg > find an item like a clue scroll or something and replace it with the new one.
